4 A BILL FOR AN ACT ENTITLED: “AN ACT GENERALLY REVISING EDUCATION TAX CREDITS;
5 ESTABLISHING A TAX CREDIT FOR PARENTS WITH CHILDREN OBTAINING EDUCATION IN A
6 NONPUBLIC SCHOOL; PROVIDING PARITY IN AGGREGATE LIMITS AVAILABLE TO ADDRESS
7 EDUCATIONAL NEEDS OF STUDENTS IN PUBLIC AND NONPUBLIC SCHOOL SETTINGS; PROVIDING A
8 DEFINITION; AMENDING SECTIONS 15-30-2303 AND 15-30-3110, MCA; AND PROVIDING AN
9 APPLICABILITY DATE AND A TERMINATION DATE.”
10
11 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF MONTANA:
12
13 NEW SECTION. Section 1. Tax credit for parents with children obtaining education in
14 nonpublic schools. (1) A resident taxpayer who is the parent or legal guardian of an eligible student is allowed
15 a credit against the tax imposed by 15-30-2103 in the amount of $250 for each eligible student each year. The
16 credit is in recognition of expenses ordinarily incurred by a parent or legal guardian of a child obtaining
17 education in a nonpublic school as described in 20-5-102(2)(e).
18 (2) The education tax credit allowed under this section may not exceed the taxpayer's income tax
19 liability but may be carried forward for 3 years. The entire amount of the tax credit not used in the year earned
20 must be carried first to the earliest tax year in which the credit may be applied and then to each succeeding tax
21 year. The credit must be claimed by filing a Montana income tax return.
22 (3) An eligible student may not be claimed by more than one taxpayer.
23 (4) The taxpayer shall attest in a manner prescribed by the department of revenue that their
24 student meets the definition of an eligible student when filing their taxes.
25 (5) For the purposes of this section, "eligible student" means a student who is:
26 (a) a Montana resident and who is 5 years of age or older on or before September 10 of the tax
27 year for which a credit is claimed and has not yet reached 19 years of age; and
28 (b) obtaining education in a nonpublic school as described in 20-5-102(2)(e).
